1
00:00:08,458 --> 00:00:09,791
[REM] But I think all
these events are related.

2
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:13,000
Your house being attacked,
your mother disappearing,

3
00:00:13,083 --> 00:00:16,291
and there're the incidents we
are dealing with at the Academy.

4
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:17,958
It would seem that
Shinko Academy

5
00:00:18,041 --> 00:00:20,291
is housing a group
of devil worshippers.

6
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:23,833
Where is the forbidden
grimoire? Tell me.

7
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,916
[RITSUKA] Maybe now the
police will believe me.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,958
[REM]
I'll call them on your behalf.

9
00:00:28,041 --> 00:00:29,291
They'll listen to me.

10
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:32,541
The authorities greatly
respect the Kaginuki name.

11
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:23,000
Are you sure I can't
change your mind?

12
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:25,125
[gasping]

13
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:26,416
Yes.

14
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,833
My brother's coming back
from England tonight,

15
00:02:28,916 --> 00:02:30,833
so I'll just hang out
with my friend Azuna

16
00:02:30,916 --> 00:02:32,583
until his flight gets in.

17
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,875
You'd be safer if you
stayed at my house.

18
00:02:34,958 --> 00:02:38,875
There's still a possibility
something might happen.

19
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:41,458
That's true.

20
00:02:41,541 --> 00:02:43,500
I'll be fine, though!

21
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:54,541
[STUDENTS chattering]

22
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:56,875
[STUDENT 2A]
Oh, Rem is here!

23
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:59,541
[STUDENT 2B]
He's beyond gorgeous!

24
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:02,541
[RITSUKA gasps]

25
00:03:03,708 --> 00:03:05,125
What is it?

26
00:03:05,208 --> 00:03:06,500
Nothing!

27
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:10,833
So, um, thank you for
putting me up for the night.

28
00:03:10,916 --> 00:03:12,458
Uh... See you later!

29
00:03:12,541 --> 00:03:14,916
--[RITSUKA panting]
--[STUDENTS chattering]

30
00:03:17,958 --> 00:03:19,916
[STUDENT 2C] Whoa! Did she just
say what I think she said?

31
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,750
[STUDENT 2AA] She's the one
that got in trouble, right?

32
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:24,250
[STUDENT 2D] I think her
name's Ritsuka Tachibana.

33
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:25,541
[STUDENT 2BB]
What'd that girl even do?

34
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:26,791
[STUDENT 2E]
Who does she think she is,

35
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:28,791
staying at the
Great Rem's house?

36
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:33,291
[RITSUKA groans] No, it's so
not what they're thinking!

37
00:03:33,375 --> 00:03:34,166
[AZUNA]
Ritsuka!

38
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:36,041
Uh!

39
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,666
Azuna!

40
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,708
Oh, thank goodness!

41
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:45,041
[AZUNA]
I was I was so worried!

42
00:03:45,125 --> 00:03:48,291
Oh, sorry about that. I'm okay.

43
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:51,875
Silly, there's nothing
to apologize for.

44
00:03:53,208 --> 00:03:58,250
[AZUNA] Wow that's crazy.
Um, any news on your mom?

45
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:00,000
[RITSUKA]
No news.

46
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:01,208
[AZUNA]
Sorry.

47
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:02,625
[RITSUKA]
Rem said he'd call the police,

48
00:04:02,708 --> 00:04:04,625
so I should hear something soon.

49
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:08,000
He's pretty influential.
Must be a Kaginuki thing.

50
00:04:08,083 --> 00:04:10,875
Yeah. I was wrong about him.

51
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,250
Huh?

52
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,416
You know, what I said yesterday.

53
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:17,458
About how the president
acted like such a jerk?

54
00:04:17,541 --> 00:04:20,458
Well, last night,
he was really great.

55
00:04:20,541 --> 00:04:22,125
Oh.

56
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,750
He tried to deny it, though.

57
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:26,666
Said he was just helping
the school. But still...

58
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,750
He saved me from those bad guys.

59
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,791
I'm so glad.

60
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:35,125
[TEACHER 2A] "If it's for
everyone's happiness,

61
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:38,750
I'm ready to have my body
burned like that Scorpion.

62
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:40,375
Even a hundred times."

63
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:43,458
[RITSUKA]
This is the same old classroom.

64
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:46,625
These are the same old lessons.

65
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:52,208
But, everything seems
so different, now.

66
00:04:52,291 --> 00:04:54,000
Oh, Mom...

67
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:58,083
[bell tolls]

68
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:03,625
[AZUNA]
Ritsuka.

69
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:05,416
Uh?

70
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:08,041
Let's go get some food.

71
00:05:08,125 --> 00:05:10,375
Sorry. I'm not very hungry.

72
00:05:10,458 --> 00:05:12,500
[AZUNA] It's important to
make sure you eat properly,

73
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:14,541
especially at times like these.

74
00:05:14,625 --> 00:05:18,250
[STUDENT 1C]
Hey Ritsuka! You're needed.

75
00:05:22,458 --> 00:05:24,166
Hello, Miss Tachibana.

76
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,416
The president has
requested your presence.

77
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:30,416
Did the police find out
where those guys took my mom?

78
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,791
Don't know

79
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,208
Hold on. You want
me to come, too?

80
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:37,375
[STUDENT 2CC]
No.

81
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:40,916
You weren't asked for.
Only Miss Tachibana.

82
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,041
'Scuse me?

83
00:05:42,125 --> 00:05:46,000
Don't worry, Azuna.
I'll be fine.

84
00:06:18,291 --> 00:06:19,500
[gasping]

85
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:31,791
Okay.

86
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:41,291
[RITSUKA]
You came to school, huh?

87
00:06:43,791 --> 00:06:45,291
[dog growls]

88
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:49,583
It's such a pleasure to see you
again my sweet little butterfly.

89
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:52,916
[dog barks]

90
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,166
You are...?

91
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,791
My name's Urie Sogami.

92
00:06:57,875 --> 00:06:59,416
Enchanté.

93
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:02,291
Y'know, you can always
ask me for help.

94
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:03,916
Forget "the Great Rem."

95
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,458
[RITSUKA]
Uh!

96
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:09,166
It would be my honor to help
such a beautiful lady like you.

97
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:09,916
[RITSUKA gasping]

98
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,041
[dog barks]

99
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,041
[gasps] I'm good.

100
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:15,083
[URIE]
Aw, you're blushing.

101
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:17,958
[SHIKI]
Enough Urie, leave her alone.

102
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:22,666
Ignore him. Hi there,
I'm Shiki Natsumezaka.

103
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:25,833
Rem told us about your woes.
You poor thing!

104
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:29,541
Please let me know if you
need anything, okay?

105
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:33,166
[SHIKI]
Such a defenseless little girl.

106
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,333
[RITSUKA]
Uh?

107
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:35,916
When I think of all
the horrible things

108
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,625
that could've possibly happened.
The thought makes me shudder.

109
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:45,583
[MAGE] Dude, can you stop being
such a creeper all the time?

110
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:49,333
Hey, I'm here if
you ever need me.

111
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:52,583
Just ask for Mage
Nanashiro, babe.

112
00:07:54,666 --> 00:07:56,250
Hands off, pal!

113
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,791
Come on!

114
00:07:57,875 --> 00:08:00,541
You're totally safe with me,
so don't even worry about it.

115
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,000
[RITSUKA]
Thanks, but no thanks!

116
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:04,416
[SHIKI laughs]
Call the wambulance,

117
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:05,583
Mage just got burned!

118
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:07,333
[MAGE] Why don't you
shut your pie hole?

119
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:08,750
[SHIKI laughing]

120
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:10,791
[URIE] Here my butterfly,
won't you enjoy this rose?

121
00:08:10,875 --> 00:08:12,875
[MAGE] She doesn't want
your stinky flower.

122
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:15,166
[URIE] Says the guy who
smells like a jockstrap!

123
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,791
[MAGE] Least I smell
like a man, pansy picker!

124
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,750
[BOTH growling]

125
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,458
[SHIKI] Wow, they're pretty
ridiculous aren't they?

126
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:24,333
But I, on the other hand...

127
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:27,458
--[SHIKI yelps]
--[dog growls]

128
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:31,583
Dumb rat! That hurt!

129
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:35,125
Do you want me to turn you
into a pair of fuzzy slippers?

130
00:08:35,208 --> 00:08:36,750
Please stop.

131
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,166
[REM]
What's going on in here?

132
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:39,541
[gasps]

133
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:46,041
[RITSUKA]
Oh, Rem, it's you!

134
00:08:46,125 --> 00:08:47,416
[SHIKI]
Uh!

135
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:50,416
Ritsuka, I just
got off the phone

136
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,791
with the police department.

137
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:59,708
So, uh, any news?

138
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,250
Yes, there is something.

139
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:04,333
They tracked your mom's last
location using her phone's GPS.

140
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:05,833
[RITSUKA]
Where is she?

141
00:09:05,916 --> 00:09:09,833
In Nagano. Not too far
from Karuizawa.

142
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,291
Nagano?

143
00:09:11,375 --> 00:09:13,333
[REM]
So you're familiar with it?

144
00:09:13,416 --> 00:09:15,458
My grandpa's house is there.

145
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:16,708
[REM]
That's interesting.

146
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:17,958
I recall you saying

147
00:09:18,041 --> 00:09:19,833
that he studied demons
and vampires, correct?

148
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:24,833
[RITSUKA] Yeah, his research
materials might still be around.

149
00:09:24,916 --> 00:09:26,625
[REM]
Then let's go.

150
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:32,500
I think it's likely
we'll find a clue

151
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:35,166
to your mother's whereabouts.

152
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:39,208
[STUDENTS chattering]

153
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:40,541
[phone rings]

154
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:41,916
Uh!

155
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:48,875
Be careful.

156
00:09:48,958 --> 00:09:51,375
[MAGE grunts]
Man, why did Rem have to go

157
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,750
and take that chick
with him to Nagano.

158
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:56,500
Seriously, a real man would
have just gone alone.

159
00:09:56,583 --> 00:09:59,125
[URIE chuckles] I wouldn't
risk underestimating him

160
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:01,625
if I were you.

161
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:04,000
If anything he took her
along because Rem knew

162
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,916
the girl might end
up being useful.

163
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,125
[MAGE]
Hm?

164
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:09,291
[URIE] It's possible our
sweet Miss Tachibana

165
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:13,041
could be hiding a clue
of which she is unaware.

166
00:10:13,125 --> 00:10:15,250
More like he took her
because the "Arlond heir"

167
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,833
gets to do whatever he wants.

168
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,166
Quiet.

169
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:21,208
You know he's known as
the "Kaginuki" heir here.

170
00:10:21,291 --> 00:10:23,958
[MAGE]
Whatever, man. I know.

171
00:10:34,041 --> 00:10:36,583
Did you get a chance
to eat lunch?

172
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,291
No, but I'm not that hungry.

173
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:46,083
You should make sure
you eat properly,

174
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:48,291
especially at times like these.

175
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:49,875
What is it?

176
00:10:49,958 --> 00:10:55,583
Oh, sorry, it's just my friend
told me the same thing earlier.

177
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:57,375
Are you going to eat it or not?

178
00:10:57,458 --> 00:11:00,000
[RITSUKA]
Uh, sure.

179
00:11:04,083 --> 00:11:07,500
It's delicious!
You've done so much for me.

180
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:10,666
Thank you. You know,
like "again."

181
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:14,166
I haven't done anything
that deserves your gratitude.

182
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,958
[RITSUKA]
But because of me you had to go

183
00:11:16,041 --> 00:11:20,916
out of your way yesterday.
And then today as well.

184
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,708
I'm unbelievably grateful.

185
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:34,166
So, um, you must be, like,
a serious dog lover.

186
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:35,250
Huh?

187
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,375
That Pomeranian at the library.

188
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:40,708
I also saw him
back at your house.

189
00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:43,958
Oh, Roen just likes to follow
me around everywhere.

190
00:11:44,041 --> 00:11:45,833
[RITSUKA]
Aw, his name is Roen?

191
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:47,750
[REM]
Do you always talk this much?

192
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,416
[RITSUKA]
Sorry.

193
00:11:57,541 --> 00:12:00,541
You don't like shitake
mushrooms?

194
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,583
I don't exactly hate them.

195
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:06,750
Okay.

196
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:08,458
But you can't really
call mushrooms food.

197
00:12:08,541 --> 00:12:09,791
When you think about it,

198
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:12,208
they're just a gross fungus
that grows on trees.

199
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:14,208
Gross fungus?

200
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:37,416
[gasps] It's over there!

201
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:55,125
[RITSUKA gasps]

202
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,958
Oh, no.

203
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:11,625
[REM] Careful, the culprits
could still be inside.

204
00:13:25,875 --> 00:13:27,666
So sad...

205
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:39,500
[gasps] My mom!

206
00:13:40,625 --> 00:13:42,458
Hey, mom?!

207
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:08,250
My mom... She's not here.

208
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:15,875
[gasps]

209
00:14:17,666 --> 00:14:19,083
[RITSUKA]
This is her phone!

210
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:21,541
That means she's
been in the house!

211
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:25,625
Oh, Mom.

212
00:14:30,083 --> 00:14:31,333
[gasps]

213
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:39,833
It'll be okay. I know
we're going to find her.

214
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,791
I think it's safe to assume
those devil worshippers

215
00:14:46,875 --> 00:14:48,625
are behind this, too.

216
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:50,958
My best guess? They're
most likely still looking

217
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:52,375
for the forbidden
grimoire they were

218
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:54,750
asking you
about last night.

219
00:14:58,208 --> 00:15:01,250
Could your grandfather
have kept it here?

220
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:03,416
Maybe. I'm not sure.

221
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:06,041
Is this grimoire really
important or something?

222
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,125
To them, apparently.

223
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:09,208
[RITSUKA]
Well grandpa kept

224
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:11,291
a lot of important
books and papers.

225
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:14,000
I suppose he could've had it.

226
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:15,833
Is there anywhere else
where he may have put

227
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:18,500
his more valuable possessions?

228
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:21,041
I honestly have no clue.

229
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:24,458
When we were little,
we'd come visit him.

230
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:27,291
I always looked forward
to spending holidays here.

231
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:29,666
Mom, Grandpa, Lindo and I,

232
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:32,750
we always had so
much fun together.

233
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,750
[REM] Is this your
mom and grandfather?

234
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:49,041
[RITSUKA] Uh. Yeah. The picture
next to them is my mom's sister.

235
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:51,500
Interesting.
Do you think your aunt

236
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:53,791
might know anything
about the grimoire?

237
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:55,375
[RITSUKA]
I wish that we could ask her,

238
00:15:55,458 --> 00:15:58,041
but she died when I was a baby.

239
00:15:58,125 --> 00:16:00,000
[REM]
I'm... sorry.

240
00:16:02,208 --> 00:16:04,666
[REM] There's no time
to clean up right now.

241
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,416
But I can't just leave it.

242
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:09,291
Tell you what, I'll send some
of my servants over later.

243
00:16:09,375 --> 00:16:10,916
You're welcome to
come with them.

244
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,666
That way you can have some help.

245
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,708
Okay, yeah, thanks.

246
00:16:22,666 --> 00:16:24,458
[RITSUKA]
I'll find you.

247
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:28,958
[gasps, grunts]

248
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:30,333
What's wrong?

249
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:32,416
The door is stuck!

250
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,833
Meaning they trapped us in.

251
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:37,458
[RITSUKA]
Uh!

252
00:16:37,541 --> 00:16:39,958
Isn't there another
exit in the kitchen?

253
00:16:40,041 --> 00:16:41,416
[RITSUKA]
Yeah.

254
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,333
[crackling]

255
00:16:47,375 --> 00:16:48,583
[REM]
Watch out.

256
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:56,208
[gasps] I'll go get
the fire extinguisher!

257
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:57,500
[REM]
No, wait!

258
00:17:09,625 --> 00:17:12,333
[gasps] No!

259
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,833
[VAMPIRE 2A laughs]

260
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,916
[RITSUKA grunts]

261
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:26,708
[REM]
Get out of here.

262
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:32,541
Fast as you can.

263
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,083
Right...

264
00:17:39,375 --> 00:17:41,708
[chuckles]

265
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:52,375
Don't tell me that's
what you call a fire.

266
00:17:52,875 --> 00:17:58,416
♪♪♪

267
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:13,875
So we meet again.

268
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:16,916
♪ All of you vulgar fellows,
hear me and begone ♪

269
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:20,000
♪ I must warn you to not
block the path I tread ♪

270
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:24,166
♪ My heart of ice ensures there
is no mercy to be shown ♪

271
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:25,916
♪ Your time is up. ♪

272
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:29,041
♪ You're nothing but
a pitiful marionette ♪

273
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:32,708
♪ Go on and dance for me
in the palm of my hand ♪

274
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:37,666
♪ Dance till the hour
of your doom ♪

275
00:18:40,916 --> 00:18:47,083
♪ I have laid claim
to this enchanting girl ♪

276
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:49,958
♪ She will be,
mine completely ♪

277
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:52,958
♪ Keep your filthy
hands off of her ♪

278
00:18:53,041 --> 00:18:58,250
♪ Behold! I'm the one
and only Rem Arlond ♪

279
00:18:58,333 --> 00:19:05,041
♪ Even the darkness bows
before the Prince of Despair! ♪

280
00:19:05,125 --> 00:19:11,875
♪ Now, this is where this
silly game comes to an end ♪

281
00:19:11,958 --> 00:19:15,375
♪ For I have declared
a checkmate ♪

282
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:17,000
♪ It's finally here ♪

283
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:21,166
♪ The end of the
dark-side game ♪

284
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,541
I let him get away again.

285
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,166
[VAMPIRE 2A groans]

286
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:31,500
Did you happen to
find the grimoire?

287
00:19:31,583 --> 00:19:33,500
[groans]

288
00:19:33,583 --> 00:19:37,833
[REM chuckels]
I'll take that as a "no."

289
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:40,208
We begin and end as dust.

290
00:19:42,458 --> 00:19:44,875
We'll call this checkmate.

291
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:46,458
[VAMPIRE 2A yelps]

292
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,416
He's still not out.

293
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:02,250
Please be okay!

294
00:20:02,333 --> 00:20:03,583
[REM]
I'm fine.

295
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:05,000
[gasps]

296
00:20:23,541 --> 00:20:25,500
[RITSUKA]
You're all right!

297
00:20:27,541 --> 00:20:30,208
Oh, Rem, I was so
worried about you!

298
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:33,625
[RITSUKA cries]

299
00:20:36,291 --> 00:20:38,750
No need to cry. I'm fine.

300
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:48,333
[EMERGENCY PERSONNEL chattering]

301
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:49,833
Why, Rem?

302
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:54,416
Why is this happening
to my family? Oh, mom.

303
00:21:07,958 --> 00:21:09,708
[REM]
Drive us home.

304
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,791
As you wish, Master.

305
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,625
[RITSUKA]
Lindo!

306
00:21:38,208 --> 00:21:41,083
Lindo! You're finally back!

307
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:47,208
It'll be okay now. I'm home.

308
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:35,583
[URIE] I know a lot of things
about your family.

309
00:23:35,666 --> 00:23:38,291
Maybe you should ask your
brother what he's hiding.

310
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:39,500
[RITSUKA]
There's no way...

311
00:23:39,583 --> 00:23:42,666
[URIE] Don't worry.
We're in my Eden now.

312
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:46,958
Act 3: "Tango of Passion
and Seduction."

